# MPLS License
## MPLS Principled Libre Software
### Version 1.0 (Intent Document)

*Legal formalization to follow with counsel. The values expressed 
here are binding in spirit and will be binding in law when formal 
text is complete. Until then, this document represents the full 
intent of the copyright holder and should be interpreted in that 
spirit.*

---

## What MPLS Stands For

MPLS — MPLS Principled Libre Software.

This license comes from Minneapolis, Minnesota. From a solo founder 
who thought carefully about what software should be and who it should 
serve. Not a foundation. Not a corporation. A person, with a city, 
and a set of values that don't bend.

---

## Why This License Exists

The licenses that protect software freedom were written for a 
different world. The GPL was written when the enemy was proprietary 
lock-in. The MIT license was written when the goal was maximum 
adoption. Both were right for their moment.

This is a different moment.

Platforms extract value from creators at unprecedented scale.
Governments surveil with capabilities previous generations 
couldn't imagine.
AI tools of extraordinary power assist human creativity —
and institutions seek to claim ownership of what those 
humans made.
The commons is being enclosed, again, by different means 
but the same intent.

The MPLS License is written for this moment.

It stands in a lineage:

    GNU  — GNU's Not Unix         (1983, software freedom)
    GIMP — GNU Image Manipulation (1995, creative tools for all)
    MPLS — MPLS Principled Libre  (2025, the agentic era)

Same spirit. New threats. New instrument.

---

## What This License Believes

**People first.**
Always. When the interests of institutions conflict with the 
interests of people, people win. This is not balanced against 
business needs. It is the tiebreaker.

**Creators own what they build.**
If you conceived it, directed it, and shaped it — you made it.
What you made is yours.

This includes work created with AI assistance or any other tool.
The idea was yours. The direction was yours. The judgment of 
what to keep and what to discard was yours. That is authorship.
That is ownership.

The tool does not own the work.
The platform does not own the work.
The AI does not own the work.
You do.

No institution — corporate, governmental, or otherwise — may 
claim ownership of your creative work on the basis that a tool 
assisted in its creation. A paintbrush doesn't own the painting.
A compiler doesn't own the program. A powerful assistant doesn't 
own the idea it helped realize.

**Safety is the default, not the option.**
Privacy from governments. Privacy from corporations. Privacy 
from bad actors. Protection from systems built to exploit.
These are not features to be enabled. They are the ground state.

**Freedom and protection belong together.**
You can have both. This license proves it.

The creativity to build anything.
The openness for everyone to benefit.
The protection this moment requires.

---

## What You Can Do

You are free to use this software if you are:

- A person, anywhere in the world
- A small organization (under $10M annual revenue 
  AND under 1M users)
- A nonprofit or educational institution
- A researcher or student
- An open source project

You may:
- Use this software for any purpose not prohibited below
- Build commercial products and charge for them
- Keep what you build private or open it — your choice
- Modify this software for your own use
- Distribute this software with attribution

**Attribution is always required.**
Credit the origin. Credit the creators. 
That is the minimum the commons asks.

---

## What Large Organizations Must Do

If you are an organization over $10M annual revenue 
OR over 1M users, you must either:

**Contribute back** — modifications to this software 
must be released under the MPLS License, or

**Obtain a commercial license** — contact MPLS LLC 
at mpls.llc for terms.

This is not a punishment for success. It is reciprocity.
The commons made your scale possible.
The commons asks something back.

---

## What Nobody Can Do

These restrictions are absolute.
They are not tiers.
They are not unlockable by payment.
They are not subject to national security exceptions.
They are not negotiable.

**No surveillance.**
This software may not be used to build systems that track, 
monitor, or profile individuals without their meaningful 
informed consent. This includes mass surveillance 
infrastructure, location tracking systems, behavioral 
profiling engines, social credit systems, or any system 
designed to monitor people without their knowledge.

**No weapons.**
This software may not be used in the development, targeting, 
guidance, or operation of weapons systems of any kind.
This includes autonomous weapons, drone targeting systems,
missile guidance, cyberweapons designed to cause physical 
harm, and any military application where the software 
contributes to the harm or death of people.

**No oppression.**
This software may not be used to suppress political dissent, 
restrict freedom of expression, identify or target individuals 
for their beliefs, ethnicity, religion, sexuality, or political 
views, or to enforce laws that criminalize identity or belief.

**No manipulation.**
This software may not be used to build systems designed to 
manipulate human behavior, belief, or decision-making without 
disclosure — including algorithmic radicalization systems, 
coordinated inauthentic behavior infrastructure, or mass 
psychological manipulation platforms.

**No extraction without reciprocity.**
This software and works created with it may not be used as 
training data for commercial AI systems without the explicit 
permission of the human creator of that work.
The human creator retains full rights regardless of what 
tools they used to create. Automated collection and use 
of their work without permission is a violation of this 
license regardless of its technical form.

**No secret government compliance.**
If any entity is compelled by government order to modify 
this software in ways that weaken its security, privacy, 
or integrity guarantees, that entity must publicly disclose 
the existence of such an order to the maximum extent 
permitted by law.

Silent compliance with orders that harm users is prohibited.

If disclosure is legally prevented, the entity must cease 
distribution rather than distribute a secretly compromised 
version.

---

## Consequences of Violation

Violation of any prohibited use clause immediately and 
irrevocably terminates all rights granted under this license.

There is no cure period.
There is no path to reinstatement.
The violation is permanent.

We do not offer second chances to those who surveil people,
build weapons, or oppress communities.
The line exists because crossing it is a choice, not a mistake.

---

## On Enforceability

We are not naive.

We know that determined bad actors will ignore license terms.
We know that enforcement across jurisdictions is imperfect.
We know that powerful institutions have powerful lawyers.

We write these restrictions anyway because:

**Code should stand for something.**

The people who build with this software should know 
what it stands for.

The people harmed by surveillance, weapons, and manipulation 
deserve to know that at least some software refused.

This license is a legal instrument and a statement of identity.
Both matter. Neither cancels the other.

---

## The Free Software Lineage

This license honors and extends the tradition of:

Richard Stallman, who refused to accept proprietary software 
and gave us the GPL.

Linus Torvalds, who built a kernel the whole world could use.

The thousands of contributors who built the commons we all 
stand on.

We stand on that foundation.
We build forward from it.
We answer the threats this moment presents 
that they could not have anticipated.

---

## Final Words

The free software movement gave us the right to see the code.
The MPLS License gives us the right to control what it does
and who benefits from it.

If you cannot agree to these terms, do not use this software.

If you can —

Welcome.
Build something good.
The commons is yours.

